.TH "build_skb_around" 9 "build_skb_around" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
build_skb_around \- build a network buffer around provided skb
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct sk_buff *" build_skb_around
.BI "(struct sk_buff *skb "  ","
.BI "void *data "  ","
.BI "unsigned int frag_size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "skb" 12
sk_buff provide by caller, must be memset cleared
.IP "data" 12
data buffer provided by caller
.IP "frag_size" 12
size of data, or 0 if head was kmalloced
